In a letter personally signed by the President, Buhari declares June 12th every year as Democracy Day and not 29th May. In line with unanimous acceptance that the election that saw Cheif MKO Abiola emerged as winner of the said June 12 election was more symbolic as Nigeria’s Democracy Day. More details below… <img src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG-20180606-WA0027-281x420.jpg" alt="" width="281" height="420" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-64566" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG-20180606-WA0027-281x420.jpg 281w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG-20180606-WA0027-100x150.jpg 100w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG-20180606-WA0027-481x720.jpg 481w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG-20180606-WA0027.jpg 722w" sizes="(max-width: 281px) 100vw, 281px" /> A.M Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. With a decade experience in Television journalism, and a graduate of University of Maiduguri. Tanimu also produces TV shows with NTA when not on Social media.